      • writeMapFromCSV

        public static boolean writeMapFromCSV(FilePath tiles,
                                      FilePath blocks,
                                      java.util.Map<java.lang.String,Tile> tileLegend,
                                      java.util.Map<java.lang.String,Block> blockLegend,
                                      java.lang.String mapDirectory,
                                      java.lang.String mapName)
                               throws java.io.FileNotFoundException
        Reads CSV (comma-separated-values) files from two FilePaths (relative to "maps/csv/<mapDirectory>"), and uses two Maps to translate them into a two-dimensional List of Tiles, and another List of Blocks. It then writes them to a map file at "maps/<mapDirectory>/<mapName>" using MapState.saveTemplateMap(String, String, List, List, Set). It returs true if it suceeded, and false otherwise. Cannot handle Entitys.
        Parameters:
        tiles - A FilePath to a CSV file with Tile data
        blocks - A FilePath to a CSV file with Block data
        tileLegend - A Map for reading the Tile file
        blockLegend - A Map for reading the Block file
        mapDirectory - The target folder to put the map file in
        mapName - The name of the map file
        Returns:
        Whether the write suceeded
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - When tiles or blocks points to a non-existent file
